Rewrite DICOM preprocessing notebook for researcher usability

notebooks/04_dataset_preprocessing.ipynb:
- Clean rewrite: 7 sections, no redundancy, consistent numbering
- Add representative frame selection (Shannon entropy) instead of
  blind first-frame — avoids blank/transition frames
- Add max_files config: None = all files, int = limit for test runs
- Make adaptive stride optional: target_frames=None keeps original
  frame count, int normalises all clips to that length
- Add optional dependency install cell (pip, commented out)
- Consolidate all helper functions into single cell (§4)
- Single-file demo (§5) with 3-row visualisation
- Batch processor (§6) respects max_files and target_frames
- NPZ inspector (§7) no longer dumps full array to output

paper/paper.md:
- Minor edits
